		<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
			<head>Biographical History</head>
			
		<p>Nathan P. Ames founded a cutlery business in Chicopee Falls, Massachusetts in 1829 which among other things provided a large number of swords by contract to the United States government.    The business relocated to Cabotville in 1834 and added a foundry which furnished most of the brass cannon for the United States army, as well as casting statues.</p></bioghist>
		
		<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
			<head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
			<p>The collection consists of two holograph letters from 1834 (about the time the factory relocated) regarding  swords ordered from Ames Manufacturing.</p>
		</scopecontent>
		
